Carol M. Browner: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 27, 2017 4:17 AM ET
Food Products

Company Overview of Bunge Limited



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Carol M. Browner  Independent Director, Bunge LimitedAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 6 Board Members in 6 different organizations across 9 different industries.See Board Relationships61$284,803
Background

		Ms. Carol M. Browner is a Senior Counselor of Albright Stonebridge Group. From 2009 to 2011, Ms. Browner served as Assistant to President Obama and Director of the White House Office of Energy and Climate Change Policy. Ms. Browner served as a Principal at Albright Capital Management LLC from 2001 to 2008. She co-founded The Albright Group LLC in 2001 and served as its Principal from 2001 to 2008. From 1991 to 1993, she served as Secretary of Florida's Department of ... Environmental Regulation. From 1993 to 2001, she served as an Head of the United States Environmental Protection Agency, where she was credited for championing common-sense, cost-effective solutions to the world's most pressing environmental and public health challenges. During her tenure as EPA Administrator, Ms. Browner enacted the strongest-ever national air pollution standards and developed the highly successful Brownfields program to clean up and redevelop abandoned, contaminated urban properties. Ms. Browner is an Attorney, is widely recognized for her innovative partnerships with the business community and non-governmental organizations, forging common sense, cost-effective solutions to public health and environmental challenges. She served as the Chairman and a Director of National Audubon Society, Inc. She also served as the Chair of the NAFTA-created US- Canada-Mexico Commission on Environmental Cooperation. Ms. Browner has been a Director at APX, Inc. since March 2008 and Independent Director of Bunge Limited since August 5, 2013. She serves as a Director of Blue292, Inc. She has been a Member of Advisory Council at General Fusion Inc. since June 2014. She serves as a Member of the advisory boards of Harvest Power, Inc. and Bloomberg Government. She serves as a Member of Advisory Board at Constella Group, LLC. She served as an Independent Director of Infosys Limited since April 2014 until November 23, 2015. Ms. Browner serves on the Executive Committee of the Center for American Progress and was a founding board member of the organization from 2003 to 2008. She serves as a distinguished senior fellow at the Center for American Progress. She is a member of the boards of The Spectrum Solutions Company and the League of Conservation Voters. She served as a Member of the President's Cabinet for eight years. She is a Member of the advisory committee of the Export-Import Bank of the United States. She is a Senior Fellow of the Aspen Institute. Ms. Browner holds a B.A. and J.D. degrees from the University of Florida.Read Full Background




